    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>lamb meatballs</strong> and cook for 2 min on each side, then turn down the heat to medium-high and cook, covered, for a further 6 min until your lamb is cooked through and browned (no pink meat!)– these are your <strong>browned lamb meatballs</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1680105154455-x200.jpg",
